```
async function* foo(){
    yield 0;
    console.log('reenter');
    await sleep(1000);
    yield 1;
}
let it = foo();
it.next();
it.next();
console.log('end');
```
Logs `end` then `reenter`, the first yield doesn't settle the iterator until after a tick

